(
<figureCitation id="7186F584245AFFF1FD600174FC578137" box="[759,932,305,329]" captionStart="Plate 16" captionStartId="47.[184,229,1270,1288]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Plate 16: Vexillum (Pusia) species, all figures 7 x Fig. 56: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Lectotype (designated herein), 8.7 mm, MTD 3152. Fig. 57: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Indonesia, Sulawesi, Lembeh Island, collected 2005 by F. Lorenz, 7.0 mm, MH. Fig. 58: Syntype 2/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 5.9 mm, MTD. Fig. 59: Type figure of Mitra tusa REEVE, 1845, Philippines, Island of Mindoro, Puerto Galero. Fig. 60: Syntype 3/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 7.4 mm, MTD. Fig. 61: Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), Philippines, Cebu, collected 2005, 8.1 mm, MH. Photos: Figs 56, 58, 60 Katrin Schniebs (MTD), Figs 57a–b, 61 Manfred Herrmann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846156/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 56–58, 60</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</heading>
<subSubSection id="A1A7BA8A245AFFF1FF490139FDDC8350" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E902E901245AFFF1FF490139FDDC8350" blockId="26.[220,1111,380,814]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Remarks: Three of 
<specimenCount id="FFBB2288245AFFF1FE210139FDA181EA" box="[438,594,380,404]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
of this species were deposited in the MTD in the Anton collection. The largest one (MTD 3152/1) was pictured in 
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F0245AFFF1FC7801E4FE6F81A0" author="Turner, H. &amp; Callomon, P." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="7 - 14" refId="ref12923" refString="Turner, H. &amp; Callomon, P. (2001): New Records of Mitriform Gastropods from Japan with Description of Vexillum (Pusia) charlesi sp. nov. (Neogastropoda: Muricoidea: Costellariidae). - Venus 60 (1 / 2): 7 - 14." type="journal article" year="2001">Turner &amp; Callomon (2001)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FE500183FDC181A0" box="[455,562,454,478]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">lectotype</typeStatus>
(fig. 10), but no formal designation was made. The other 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FED801A9FE45827A" box="[335,438,492,516]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntypes</typeStatus>
were not mentioned in that paper. The 
<taxonomicName id="2EBD9282245AFFF1FCE701A9FBF8827A" authorityName="MACDONALD" authorityYear="1860" box="[880,1035,492,516]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Costellariidae</taxonomicName>
types in the Anton collection were presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F0245AFFF1FD470254FC7D8257" author="Schniebs, K." box="[720,910,529,553]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="39 - 42" refId="ref12690" refString="Schniebs, K. (2003): Die Typen und Typoide der Molluskensammlung der Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden, Museum fur Tierkunde (I), Die Typen der von Anton (1838) beschriebenen rezenten Mollusken: 7. Helicinidae, Costellariidae, Tellinidae, Corbiculidae, Veneridae, Corbulidae, Petricolidae, Pholadidae. - Malakologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden 21: 39 - 42." type="journal article" year="2003">Schniebs (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. Three 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FC7E0254FBA28257" box="[1001,1105,529,553]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntypes</typeStatus>
are mentioned and again the largest one (
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FD2E0273FCFE8230" box="[697,781,566,590]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="8.7">8.7 mm</quantity>
x 
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FCB10273FC8D8230" box="[806,894,566,590]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
) is pictured. When investigating these 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FE560219FDDE820A" box="[449,557,604,628]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntypes</typeStatus>
, the authors of the present paper identified the two smaller 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FEFF02C4FE3C82E7" box="[360,463,641,665]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntypes</typeStatus>
MTD 3152/2 (
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FDE702C4FD3282E7" box="[624,705,641,665]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="7.4">7.4 mm</quantity>
x 3.0 mm, 
<figureCitation id="7186F584245AFFF1FCAC02C4FC7582E7" box="[827,902,641,665]" captionStart="Plate 16" captionStartId="47.[184,229,1270,1288]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Plate 16: Vexillum (Pusia) species, all figures 7 x Fig. 56: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Lectotype (designated herein), 8.7 mm, MTD 3152. Fig. 57: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Indonesia, Sulawesi, Lembeh Island, collected 2005 by F. Lorenz, 7.0 mm, MH. Fig. 58: Syntype 2/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 5.9 mm, MTD. Fig. 59: Type figure of Mitra tusa REEVE, 1845, Philippines, Island of Mindoro, Puerto Galero. Fig. 60: Syntype 3/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 7.4 mm, MTD. Fig. 61: Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), Philippines, Cebu, collected 2005, 8.1 mm, MH. Photos: Figs 56, 58, 60 Katrin Schniebs (MTD), Figs 57a–b, 61 Manfred Herrmann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846156/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) and MTD 3152/3 (
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FF7202E3FECA82C0" box="[229,313,678,702]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
x 
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FEC102E3FE5E82C0" box="[342,429,678,702]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
, 
<figureCitation id="7186F584245AFFF1FE2E02E3FDF582C0" box="[441,518,678,702]" captionStart="Plate 16" captionStartId="47.[184,229,1270,1288]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Plate 16: Vexillum (Pusia) species, all figures 7 x Fig. 56: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Lectotype (designated herein), 8.7 mm, MTD 3152. Fig. 57: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Indonesia, Sulawesi, Lembeh Island, collected 2005 by F. Lorenz, 7.0 mm, MH. Fig. 58: Syntype 2/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 5.9 mm, MTD. Fig. 59: Type figure of Mitra tusa REEVE, 1845, Philippines, Island of Mindoro, Puerto Galero. Fig. 60: Syntype 3/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 7.4 mm, MTD. Fig. 61: Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), Philippines, Cebu, collected 2005, 8.1 mm, MH. Photos: Figs 56, 58, 60 Katrin Schniebs (MTD), Figs 57a–b, 61 Manfred Herrmann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846156/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) as 
<taxonomicName id="2EBD9282245AFFF1FDAE02E3FC1082C0" authority="(REEVE, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="REEVE" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[569,995,678,702]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tusum" subGenus="Pusia">
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FDAE02E3FD6B82C0" box="[569,664,678,702]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Vexillum</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FD3E02E3FD1582C0" box="[681,742,678,702]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Pusia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FD6F02E3FCCD82C0" box="[760,830,678,702]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">tusum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F0245AFFF1FCD802E3FC2F82C0" author="Reeve, L. A." box="[847,988,678,702]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref12476" refString="Reeve, L. A. (1845): Monograph of the genus Mitra. Vol. 2. - London." type="book" year="1845">REEVE, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. To avoid further confusion, we exclude those specimens from the type lot and designate the largest 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FECA02B4FE458377" box="[349,438,753,777]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntype</typeStatus>
(
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FE5102B4FDEA8377" box="[454,537,753,777]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="8.7">8.7 mm</quantity>
x 
<quantity id="2E4544E4245AFFF1FDA402B4FD788377" box="[563,651,753,777]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
, 
<figureCitation id="7186F584245AFFF1FD0202B4FD138377" box="[661,736,753,777]" captionStart="Plate 16" captionStartId="47.[184,229,1270,1288]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Plate 16: Vexillum (Pusia) species, all figures 7 x Fig. 56: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Lectotype (designated herein), 8.7 mm, MTD 3152. Fig. 57: Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838), Indonesia, Sulawesi, Lembeh Island, collected 2005 by F. Lorenz, 7.0 mm, MH. Fig. 58: Syntype 2/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 5.9 mm, MTD. Fig. 59: Type figure of Mitra tusa REEVE, 1845, Philippines, Island of Mindoro, Puerto Galero. Fig. 60: Syntype 3/3 of Vexillum (Pusia) semicostatum (ANTON, 1838) = Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), excluded from the type lot MTD 3152, 7.4 mm, MTD. Fig. 61: Vexillum (Pusia) tusum (REEVE, 1845), Philippines, Cebu, collected 2005, 8.1 mm, MH. Photos: Figs 56, 58, 60 Katrin Schniebs (MTD), Figs 57a–b, 61 Manfred Herrmann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846156/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) as 
<typeStatus id="360657A3245AFFF1FC8702B4FC8B8377" box="[784,888,753,777]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="2EBD9282245AFFF1FC0B02B4FDD98350" authority="(ANTON, 1838)" baseAuthorityName="ANTON" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="semicostatum" subGenus="Pusia">
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FC0B02B4FC088377" box="[924,1019,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Vexillum</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FB9C02B4FBBB8377" box="[1035,1096,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Pusia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DBC93513245AFFF1FF490353FE8E8350" box="[222,381,790,814]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">semicostatum</emphasis>
(ANTON, 1838)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
